cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on studying the performance of TCP protocol in networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category as network performance is closely related to security and cryptography. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of understanding the global behavior of the Internet and its networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the performance of information transmission over networks. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper proposes a new method for studying the performance of TCP protocol.
